{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772458622,"nonce":"iyN0wo4qlVCKQuMSpbzHn0tCjk4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vGAJe","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/324","origin":"github"},"title":"Rename env.sh to setup.sh to mirror ROS workspace conventions","message":"## Context\n\nPart of #263 (Simplify scripts and Makefile interface). The owner has requested that `env.sh` be renamed to `setup` to mirror the convention used by ROS workspace setup scripts (e.g. `install/setup.bash`).\n\n## Problem\n\n`.agent/scripts/env.sh` is referenced by its current name in four places:\n\n- `AGENTS.md` — script reference table and inline usage examples\n- `CLAUDE.md` — environment setup section\n- `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — environment setup section\n- `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md` — environment setup section\n\nThe `env.sh` script also contains the `git checkout` guardrail (enforcement, not just environment setup), so the rename must preserve that behaviour.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Rename `.agent/scripts/env.sh` → `.agent/scripts/setup.sh`\n2. Update all references in:\n   - `AGENTS.md` (script reference table + inline examples)\n   - `CLAUDE.md`\n   - `.github/copilot-instructions.md`\n   - `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md`\n3. Verify the checkout guardrail still functions after the rename\n4. Add a compatibility shim (symlink or forwarding script) if needed to avoid breaking existing agent sessions that still source the old path — or document the migration clearly\n\n## Constraints\n\n- The checkout guardrail (`git checkout` is blocked by this script) must remain functional\n- All framework adapter files must stay in sync (ADR-0006)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**Model**: `claude-sonnet-4.6`","files":null}]}